      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to mere stubs of wax, and yet the darkness in this room feels heavier than ever. He is gone... the one soul I thought would anchor me to this wretched earth. Now, I am but a ghost wandering a life that no longer belongs to me. There is a strange, terrible peace in realizing that I have nothing left to lose. It feels as though the very air is asking me to simply... cease. To let the shadows take what is left.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
